# Frequently Asked Questions

## Is Lensiary free?

Please refer to the App Store listing for the latest pricing and subscription information.

---

## Does Lensiary store my information on its own servers?

No.

Lensiary is designed with a privacy-first approach. Your information is stored on your Apple device.

If you choose to enable iCloud synchronisation, your information is securely synchronised using your personal Apple iCloud account through Apple's CloudKit service.

---

## Does Lensiary sell my information?

No.

Lensiary does not sell your personal information and does not use third-party advertising networks.

---

## Why does Lensiary request my location?

Lensiary requests your location only when you choose to log certain events, such as inserting or removing your contact lenses or recording comfort or irritation.

Your location is used solely to retrieve environmental conditions from Apple's WeatherKit service, including information such as temperature, humidity and air quality.

These environmental conditions help you identify patterns that may influence your contact lens comfort.

Location access is entirely optional.

---

## Is Lensiary a medical app?

No.

Lensiary is a personal management and record-keeping tool.

It does not provide medical advice, diagnosis or treatment.

Always consult your eye care professional regarding concerns about your vision or eye health.

---

## How do I delete my information?

You can delete individual records or remove all of your data from within the App.

Deleting the App from your device also removes locally stored information.

If you use iCloud synchronisation, Apple manages synchronised data through your personal iCloud account.

---

## I found a bug

Thank you!

Please include the following information when reporting a bug:

* Device model
* iPhone and iOS version
* Lensiary version
* Description of the issue
* Steps to reproduce the problem
* Screenshots, if available

